**1. How to check OTG connection is enabled or not**

Android&#39;s internal setting database contains this information. The variable used to store the value is different from phone to phone. This option is available in OPPO, REALME, ONEPLUS, and VIVO. For most of the phones, you can use the below code to check whether it is enabled or not

     public boolean iSOTGConnectionEnabled()
    {
        try {
            //all latest version
            String value = Settings.Global.getString(getContentResolver(),&quot;persist.sys.oplus.otg_support&quot;);
            if(value==null)
            {
                //old oppo,realme
                value = Settings.Global.getString(getContentResolver(),&quot;sys.oppo.otg_support&quot;);
                if(value==null)
                {
                    //old oneplus phone
                    value = Settings.Global.getString(getContentResolver(),&quot;persist.sys.oem.otg_support&quot;);
                }
            }
            if(value!=null)
            {
                if(Integer.parseInt(value) == 0)
                {
                    return false;
                }
            }
        }catch (Exception e){}
        return true;
    }


To identify this variable name, you can use any &#39;setting database editor&#39; app from play store and search for &#39;otg&#39;

